      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid properties) must be reproduced in the CFD model within ±5% of nominal values.",
      "rationale": "FDA benchmark experimental conditions were reproduced in the CFD model using measured fluid properties (glycerol-water mixture at 37°C, viscosity 3.5 mPa·s, density 1050 kg/m³). Inlet flow rates and rotational speeds were set to within 0.5% of the reported experimental values."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metrics (MAPE, normalized RMS error) must be computed for all primary QoIs against experimental reference data.",
      "rationale": "MAPE of 4.2% for pump pressure rise and normalized RMS error of 6.8% for velocity profiles at the impeller exit plane were computed against FDA experimental data. Both metrics satisfy the ±10% acceptance criterion established for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs used in validation must be directly traceable to the clinical endpoint (hemolysis) and the regulatory acceptance criterion (RH < 1).",
      "rationale": "The normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) and relative hemolysis index (RH) are the primary QoIs. RH is directly specified in the regulatory submission acceptance criterion and is computed from the power-law hemolysis model applied to CFD-predicted shear stress and exposure time fields. Traceability to clinical hemolysis endpoints is documented."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
