      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The turbulence model and hemolysis sub-model must be justified against available literature and benchmark data for rotating blood-contacting devices.",
      "rationale": "The SST k-omega turbulence model was selected based on published benchmarking for rotating machinery and blood pump flows. The Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model is the de facto standard for CFD hemolysis prediction in regulatory submissions. Model form uncertainty was assessed through comparison of SST k-omega against realizable k-epsilon at two operating points, yielding less than 8% difference in NIH."
    },
