    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed the required levels for MRL 2. The six non-assessed factors are appropriately scoped out per the MRL 2 credibility plan for a Class II device. Validation results demonstrate MAPE of 4.2% for hydraulic performance and RH < 1.0 for hemolysis index across all five operating points. The grid convergence study confirms GCI < 3% for the primary QoI. The overall evidence body is sufficient to support the claim that the CFD model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the CPB device. Decision: Accepted.",
